						               													<description>Miniatures wargame rules for any semihistorical or fictional setting where close combat remains important (so including many forms of soft science fiction alongside typical fantasy).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unrelated to any particular setting or range of miniatures, Last Stand divide all troops into a number of generic troop types amalgamating equipment, tactics, morale, etc. An army will contain about 25-60 stands of troops depending on types. Stands can be of different sizes but it is recommended that both sides stick to the same.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sequence of play is an unusual continuous model rather than the more traditional fixed and repetitious order of conducting events.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are aimed primarily at one-on-one play but solo, pairs, or teams play is possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
